The characteristic equation is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left|\begin{array}{cc}
-7-\lambda & -4\\
6 & 7-\lambda
\end{array}\right| & =(-7-\lambda)(7-\lambda)-(-4)(6)\\
 & =-49+\lambda^{2}+24\\
 & =\lambda^{2}-25=0
\end{align*}

\end_inset

so the eigenvalues are 
\begin_inset Formula $-5$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $5$
\end_inset

.
 Eigenvectors are found by reducing the matrices
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
-2 & -4\\
6 & 12
\end{array}\right]\quad\text{and}\quad\left[\begin{array}{cc}
-12 & -4\\
6 & 2
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset

to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
-2 & -4\\
0 & 0
\end{array}\right]\quad\text{and}\quad\left[\begin{array}{cc}
-12 & -4\\
0 & 0
\end{array}\right],
\]

\end_inset

which gives eigenvectors of the forms 
\begin_inset Formula $x=-2y$
\end_inset

